title: Free Trade Agreements
description:
While free trade agreements can be a source of significant cost savings, the effort of administering a preferential program is not always worth the perceived gain.

Taking advantage of preferential programs can also create risk of non-compliance due to the complexity of trade rules.
 
This risk or lack of manpower to utilize such programs can be overcome by leveraging technology.

Amber Road’s global trade management software automates the process in 4 steps:

1. Trade agreement identification:
Identification of preferential programs within your global trade lanes and projected cost savings.

2. Supplier solicitation campaigns:
Automated collection of product information from suppliers for rules of origin qualification.

3. Bill of material qualification:
Compilation of supplier’s information in a Bill of Materials certificate to generate the correct customs documentation.

4. Certificate management:
Managing certificates for origin updates, renewals and audits.

There are over 500 global trade programs. Learn more in this eBook: https://info.amberroad.com/rs/665-BWT-776/images/Amber%20Road%20The%20Why%20and%20How%20on%20the%20Path%20to%20FTAs%20eBook%20EU.pdf
